StringBuilder and stringBuffer
// 1) Mutability:  String is immutable but str builder/buffer is mutable

// 2) string stores in String constant pool and Str bui/buff stores in heap memory

// 3) IMP : Thread Safety
/* String: Not used in threaded environment as it is immutable
    StringBuilder: Not thread safe so it is used in a single-threaded environment.
    StringBuffer: Thread safe so it is used in a multi-threaded environment.
 */

// 4) IMP : Speed
/* String: Comparatively slowest
    stringBuffer: faster than string but slower than stringBuilder
    stringBuilder: Comparatively faster
*/


