            Imports and packages:
            A package in Java is a namespace that groups related classes, interfaces, enums, and sub-packages together.
            Types of Packages -->
            - Built-in Packages: java. lang,util,io,sql,net
            - User-Defined Packages:  package com.college.exam;
            An import statement allows a Java program to access classes defined in other packages without using their full package name.
            Eg. import java.util.Scanner;       Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
            Types of Import Statements
            - Single-Class Import
                import java.util.Scanner;
            - Wildcard Import
                import java.util.*;
            Note: java.lang (automatically imported)

            Access Modifiers:
            Types: public, protected, default (no modifier), private
            public: Everywhere
            protected: Same package + subclasses
            default: Same package
            private: Within the same class only

