FileWriter
It is a Java class used to write character data (text) into a file.
Common methods:
write(int c) --> Writes Single character
write(String s) --> Writes String
write(char[] c) --> Writes char array
flush() --> forces writing
close() --> closes stream


FileReader
FileReader class is used for reading streams of characters from files.
It is a character based stream meaning it reads character.
Common Methods:
read(): reads a single character and return it as integer. return -1 if the end of the stream (flow) is reached
read(char[] buf): reads characters into an array and returns a number of characters read.

#Collections

List Interface methods:
add(E e):Appends the specified element
add(int index, E element): Insert at specified position
remove(Object o): Removes the first occurrence of the specified element
remove(int index): removes the first occurrence of the specified element
get(int index): return the element at the specified position
set(int index, E element): replaces the element at the specified position
size(): return the number of elements
clear(): removes all of the elements
contains(Object o): returns 'true' if the list contains the specified element
indexOf(Object o): returns the index of the first occurrence, or -1 if the list does not contain the element.

Queue Interface:
add(E e): Inserts the specified element into the queue. Throws an exception if the element cannot be added
offer(E e): Inserts the specified element into the queue. returns false if the element cannot be added
remove(): retrives and removes the head of the queue. throws an exception if the queue is empty
poll(): retrives and removes the head of the queue, or returns null if the queue is empty
element(): retrieves, but does not remove, the head of the queue. Throws an exception if the queue is empty.
peek(): retrieves, but does not remove, the head of the queue, or return null if the queue is empty.

Set Interface:
add(E e): Adds the specified element from the set
remove(Object o): Removes the specified element from the set
contains(Object o): checks if the set contains the specified element
size(): return the number of element in the set
isEmpty(): checks if thw set is empty

